Catacombs of Paris - Wikipedia|https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Catacombs_of_Paris|]) are underground ossuaries in Paris, France, which hold the remains of more than six million people. Built to consolidate Paris's ancient stone quarries, they extend south from the Barrière d'Enfer("Gate of Hell") former city gate. The ossuary was created as part of the effort to eliminate the effects of the city's overflowing cemeteries. Preparation work began shortly after a 1774 series of basement wall  ...    and from 1788, nightly processions of covered wagons transferred remains from most of Paris's cemeteries to a mine  ...    ; Catacombs of Paris is located in Paris, Catacombs of Paris, Location within Paris ; - ; ; Established ; 1810 ; ; Location ; Place Denfert-Rochereau, 75014 Paris, France ;  ...    ## History  ### Paris's cemeteries  Les Innocents cemetery in 1550 Paris's earliest burial grounds were to the southern outskirts of the Roman-era Left Bank city. In ruins  ...    invasions. When it became its own parish associated with the church of the " Saints Innocents"
